Error: Error: "Connection Failed: SSL Certificate Problem: Self Signed Certificate In Certificate Chain" When Trying To Connect To A Pterodactyl Minecraft Server.

Solution: This error occurs when the SSL certificate used by the Pterodactyl panel is self-signed and not authenticated by a trusted certificate authority. To fix this error, follow these steps:

Step 1: Download the SSL certificate from the Pterodactyl panel using your web browser. This can be done by navigating to the panel
